    <h2>Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p><strong>Effective Date:</strong> March 26, 2025</p>
    <p>At illegible.ink ("we," "us," or "our"), we value your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our web application ("Service"), which is powered by Spotify.</p>

    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>We collect only the following information:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>User ID:</strong> Your Spotify user ID, obtained through Spotify authentication, to identify you within our Service.</li>
      <li><strong>Purchased Sets:</strong> Records of the playlists you purchase, stored with your user ID and purchase date.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not collect any other personal information beyond what is necessary to provide the Service.</p>

    <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>
    <p>We use your information solely to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Authenticate your Spotify account and enable access to the Service.</li>
      <li>Track your purchased playlist sets to provide you with access to them.</li>
      <li>Fulfill your requests to save purchased playlists to your Spotify account.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>3. Data Storage and Security</h3>
    <p>Your user ID and purchased sets are stored in a secure SQLite database. We implement reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your data from unauthorized access, loss, or disclosure. However, no system is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</p>

    <h3>4. Sharing Your Information</h3>
    <p>We do not share, sell, or disclose your personal information to third parties, except:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>With Spotify, to authenticate your account and save playlists, as required by the Service.</li>
      <li>As required by law or to comply with legal processes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>5. Your Rights</h3>
    <p>You may request deletion of your data (user ID and purchased sets) at any time via the "Delete My Data" button in the Service. Upon request, we will promptly delete your information from our database.</p>

    <h3>6. Third-Party Services</h3>
    <p>Our Service is powered by Spotify. Your use of Spotify is subject to Spotify’s <a href="https://www.spotify.com/legal/privacy-policy/" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>. We use Stripe for payment processing, subject to Stripe’s <a href="https://stripe.com/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

    <h3>7. Changes to This Policy</h3>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Your continued use of the Service constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</p>

    <h3>8. Contact Us</h3>
